---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const seo = {
  title: '10 Best Local Listing Management Tools in 2026',
  description: 'The best local listing management tools to sync business data, fix inconsistencies, suppress duplicates, and monitor accuracy across directories. Winner: theStacc.',
  canonical: 'https://thestacc.com/best/local-listing-management-tools/',
  ogImage: '/og/best/local-listing-management-tools.png',
  schemaData: [
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
      "itemListElement": [
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://thestacc.com/" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Best", "item": "https://thestacc.com/best/" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Best Local Listing Management Tools", "item": "https://thestacc.com/best/local-listing-management-tools/" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "ItemList",
      "name": "10 Best Local Listing Management Tools in 2026",
      "itemListOrder": "https://schema.org/ItemListOrderDescending",
      "numberOfItems": 10,
      "itemListElement": [
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "theStacc", "url": "https://thestacc.com/" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Yext" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Moz Local" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 4, "name": "BrightLocal" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 5, "name": "Semrush Listing Management" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 6, "name": "Whitespark" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 7, "name": "Synup" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 8, "name": "SE Ranking" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 9, "name": "Uberall" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 10, "name": "Birdeye" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "FAQPage",
      "mainEntity": [
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What is the best local listing management tool in 2026?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "theStacc is our top pick for local listing management in 2026. It goes beyond listing sync by creating 30 GBP posts and 30 blog articles per month on autopilot — the content that improves your local pack rankings after your listings are accurate. Pair theStacc with Yext ($499/yr) or Moz Local ($20/mo) for complete listing management plus content creation." }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What is local listing management?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Local listing management ensures your business name, address, and phone number (NAP data) is consistent and accurate across all directories, maps, and apps where customers find you — Google, Apple Maps, Bing, Yelp, Facebook, and 50–200+ others. Inconsistent NAP data confuses Google and lowers your local pack rankings." }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Why does local listing accuracy matter for SEO?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Google cross-references your business data across directories to verify its accuracy. One wrong phone number on Yelp, an outdated address on Apple Maps, or a duplicate listing with different information all send conflicting signals that lower your local search rankings. Consistent, accurate listings across 50+ directories strengthen Google's trust in your business data." }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What is the difference between Yext and Moz Local?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yext distributes your listing data to 200+ directories in real time and suppresses duplicates — but costs $499/year and reverts listings if you cancel. Moz Local covers 90+ directories at $20–$40/month and includes data aggregator submissions. Yext is better for large multi-location businesses; Moz Local is better for single-location businesses on a budget." }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Do I need a listing management tool if I have Google Business Profile?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. GBP is one listing. Customers and Google cross-reference 50–200+ other directories. Apple Maps, Bing, Yelp, Facebook, Healthgrades, TripAdvisor, and data aggregators like Factual and Acxiom all need accurate NAP data. Tools like Yext or Moz Local handle these automatically; without them, you're managing each directory manually." }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What are data aggregators and why do they matter?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Data aggregators (Factual, Acxiom, Neustar, Localeze) are companies that collect business data and distribute it to hundreds of downstream directories. If your data is wrong at the aggregator level, it spreads incorrect information to dozens of sites automatically. Moz Local and some Yext plans submit corrections to aggregators directly, fixing the source." }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Can I manage local listings manually instead of paying for a tool?",
          "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes, but it's time-consuming. The 6 directories that drive most local traffic (Google, Facebook, Apple Maps, Bing, Yelp, Foursquare) can be updated manually. For 50–200+ directories, manual management requires hours per update cycle. Tools like Moz Local at $20/month make the math simple: one hour of your time is worth more than the subscription." }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
};
---
<BaseLayout seo={seo}>

  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="hero-section">
    <a href="/best/" class="hero-pill">
      <span class="pill-dot"></span>
      <span>Best of 2026 · Updated this quarter</span>
      <span class="pill-arrow">→</span>
    </a>
    <h1 class="h-display">10 Best <span class="accent">Local Listing Management Tools</span> in 2026 (Tested &amp; Ranked)</h1>
    <p class="hero-sub">We tested 10 local listing management tools — directory sync, duplicate suppression, data accuracy monitoring, and citation building — across 70+ industries. Here's the full ranked list, from the tool that drives rankings to the tool that syncs 200+ directories.</p>
    <div class="hero-ctas">
      <a href="/checkout/" class="btn btn-primary"><span>Try the #1 pick — $1 trial <span class="arrow">→</span></span></a>
      <a href="#ranked-list" class="btn btn-secondary">See the full ranking</a>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-meta">
      <div class="hero-meta-item">
        <span><strong>10 tools</strong> tested for listing sync, accuracy, and ranking impact</span>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-meta-item">
        <span><strong>70+ industries</strong> · dentists, lawyers, HVAC, restaurants</span>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-meta-item">
        <span>Last updated <strong>Q2 2026</strong></span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- QUICK VERDICT BOX -->
  <section class="modules-bento">
    <div class="modules-tabs-header">
      <span class="label-pill">Quick verdict · 3 picks</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">Three tools for three listing management problems. <span class="accent">Start here.</span></h2>
      <p class="lede">One drives rankings through content. One syncs 200+ directories. One audits what's broken. The full list and comparison table are below.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bento-grid">
      <a class="bento-card bento-feature" href="/checkout/">
        <div class="bento-num">01</div>
        <div class="bento-icon">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polygon points="12 2 15.09 8.26 22 9.27 17 14.14 18.18 21.02 12 17.77 5.82 21.02 7 14.14 2 9.27 8.91 8.26 12 2"/></svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="bento-title">Overall winner: theStacc</h3>
        <h4 class="bento-sub">The best tool for <span class="accent">local ranking after your listings are accurate</span> — 30 GBP posts + 30 blog articles per month from $49/mo.</h4>
        <p class="bento-desc">Accurate listings are the foundation. But consistent NAP data alone won't get you to the top of the local pack. theStacc creates the GBP content and blog articles that improve your local rankings on top of that foundation. 30 GBP posts + 30 blog articles per month, fully automated, for $126/month bundled.</p>
        <ul class="bento-list">
          <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>30 GBP posts/month keeping your profile active for Maps rankings</li>
          <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>30 blog articles/month building topical authority and organic traffic</li>
          <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Content optimized for "[service] in [city]" local keywords</li>
          <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>$1 trial · No contract · Cancel anytime</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="bento-mock">
          <div class="bento-mock-bar">
            <div class="bento-mock-meta">THESTACC · #1 OVERALL · FROM $49/MO</div>
            <span class="bento-mock-pulse"></span>
          </div>
          <div class="bento-mock-title">60 pieces of local content per month — GBP + blog combined</div>
          <div class="bento-mock-tags">
            <span class="bento-mock-tag brand">$126/mo bundle</span>
            <span class="bento-mock-tag">30 GBP posts</span>
            <span class="bento-mock-tag brand">30 articles</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="bento-cta">Start the $1 trial <span class="arrow">→</span></div>
      </a>

      <a class="bento-card" href="#tool-2">
        <div class="bento-num">02</div>
        <h3 class="bento-title">Best directory sync: Yext</h3>
        <h4 class="bento-sub">For multi-location businesses that need <span class="accent">real-time sync across 200+ directories</span> from ~$499/year.</h4>
        <p class="bento-desc">Yext's Knowledge Graph creates one source of truth for all your business data and pushes updates to 200+ platforms instantly. Duplicate suppression, holiday hours management, photo distribution — all from one dashboard.</p>
        <div class="bento-cta">See full review <span class="arrow">↓</span></div>
      </a>

      <a class="bento-card" href="#tool-4">
        <div class="bento-num">04</div>
        <h3 class="bento-title">Best listing audit: BrightLocal</h3>
        <h4 class="bento-sub">For businesses that want to <span class="accent">audit what's broken</span> before investing in a distribution tool — from $39/mo.</h4>
        <p class="bento-desc">BrightLocal's citation tracker audits NAP data across 80+ directories, flags every inconsistency, and tells you exactly what to fix before you spend money on distribution.</p>
        <div class="bento-cta">See full review <span class="arrow">↓</span></div>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- METHODOLOGY -->
  <section class="problem-section">
    <div class="problem-header">
      <span class="label-pill">How we tested</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">We tested <span class="accent">10 listing management tools</span> across real local businesses in 70+ industries.</h2>
      <p>Local listing management is not glamorous. But wrong information scattered across directories is one of the most common reasons local businesses underperform in search. One wrong phone number on Yelp means lost calls. An outdated address on Apple Maps sends customers to the wrong location. We tested how well each tool prevents these silent revenue leaks.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="ba-grid">
      <div class="ba-col before">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">What we measured</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">5 criteria. Same scorecard for all 10.</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">Applied across every tool we tested.</p>
        </div>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">01</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Directory Coverage</h4>
              <p>How many directories, maps, and apps does the tool sync to? More coverage means fewer gaps where customers find wrong information.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">02</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Data Sync Speed</h4>
              <p>How quickly do updates propagate after you change business information? Slow sync means customers see outdated hours, addresses, or phone numbers for weeks.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">03</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Duplicate Suppression</h4>
              <p>Can it find and remove conflicting or duplicate listings? Duplicates confuse Google and split your review authority across profiles.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">04</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Accuracy Monitoring</h4>
              <p>Does it alert you when third-party edits override your data? Directories accept user-submitted changes that can overwrite your correct information.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">05</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Price Per Location</h4>
              <p>What does a single-location business actually pay per month? Listing tools charge per location — costs multiply fast for multi-location businesses.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="ba-col after">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">What we found</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Listing accuracy is the floor, not the ceiling.</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">Three findings from testing 10 tools.</p>
        </div>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">01</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Most businesses are missing listings on 10+ directories</h4>
              <p>The average local business we tested had correct information on 6–8 major platforms but wrong or missing data on 15–30 secondary directories that aggregators and niche apps reference.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">02</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Data aggregators are the source of most cascading errors</h4>
              <p>Wrong data on Factual, Acxiom, or Localeze spreads to dozens of downstream directories automatically. Fixing aggregators (Moz Local's strength) is more efficient than fixing each directory manually.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">03</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Listing accuracy alone doesn't win rankings — content does</h4>
              <p>Businesses with accurate listings but no content still lost local pack positions to competitors publishing regular GBP posts and blog articles. Listings are necessary but not sufficient.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">04</span>
            <div>
              <h4>The best setup combines a listing tool with a content tool</h4>
              <p>Yext or Moz Local for listing accuracy + theStacc for content creation covers both the foundation and the ranking driver for under $170/month combined.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">05</span>
            <div>
              <h4>BrightLocal audit before Yext subscription saves most businesses money</h4>
              <p>Run a BrightLocal audit first. You might find only 5–6 directories need fixing — solvable manually for free, with no Yext subscription needed.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- STATS ROW -->
  <section>
    <div class="stats-row">
      <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-num">10<span class="accent"></span></div><div class="stat-label">Listing tools tested · 70+ industries</div></div>
      <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-num">200<span class="accent">+</span></div><div class="stat-label">Directories synced by top tool (Yext)</div></div>
      <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-num">$20<span class="accent">/mo</span></div><div class="stat-label">Most affordable listing sync (Moz Local)</div></div>
      <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-num">$49<span class="accent">/mo</span></div><div class="stat-label">theStacc GBP content automation</div></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- RANKED LIST -->
  <section class="problem-section" id="ranked-list">
    <div class="problem-header">
      <span class="label-pill">The full ranked list</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">10 local listing management tools, <span class="accent">ranked by ranking impact, coverage, and value.</span></h2>
      <p>Each entry: rank, name, price, who it fits, one-paragraph verdict, three pros, one honest con. No hedging.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="tool-1">
      <div class="ba-col after" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#1 · WINNER · FROM $49/MO</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">theStacc — Best Tool for Improving Local Rankings After Listings Are Accurate</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For local businesses that have accurate listings and now need the content that moves them up the local pack.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">Accurate listings are the foundation of local SEO. But they're a floor, not a ceiling. Once your NAP data is consistent across directories, the businesses climbing the local pack are the ones publishing consistent content. theStacc publishes 30 GBP posts per month and 30 blog articles per month on autopilot. The Local SEO module ($49/mo) handles GBP content. The Blog SEO module ($99/mo) handles website content. Bundle both for ~$126/month and get 60 pieces of local content — more output than most agencies deliver for $2,000–$5,000/month.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">✓</span>
            <div>
              <h4>30 GBP posts + 30 blog articles per month — fully automated</h4>
              <p>Content targeted to your business, industry, and location. Posts cover local queries like "[service] in [city]" and "best [service] near me." Articles build topical authority that drives both organic traffic and Maps prominence.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">✓</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Drives the ranking factors listing tools don't cover</h4>
              <p>Listing tools handle NAP accuracy. theStacc handles content freshness and GBP activity — two of the three controllable Maps ranking factors. Together, they cover the full local SEO foundation.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">✓</span>
            <div>
              <h4>$126/mo bundle — no contracts, $1 trial, cancel anytime</h4>
              <p>Pair with Moz Local at $20/month for listing distribution and you have both pillars of local SEO covered for $146/month total. More output than a $2,000/month agency, for 7% of the cost.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">✗</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Honest con: no directory listing management or citation building</h4>
              <p>theStacc creates content. It does not sync directories, build citations, or suppress duplicate listings. Pair with Moz Local ($20/mo) or Yext ($499/yr) for listing accuracy alongside theStacc's content engine.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <div style="margin-top: 24px;">
          <a href="/checkout/" class="btn btn-primary"><span>Start the $1 trial <span class="arrow">→</span></span></a>
          <a href="/modules/local-seo/" class="btn btn-secondary" style="margin-left: 12px;">See Local SEO module</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="tool-2" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#2 · ~$499/YR · ANNUAL CONTRACT</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Yext — Best Multi-Directory Sync for Enterprise and Multi-Location</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For franchise groups and multi-location businesses that need real-time listing data across 200+ directories.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">Yext is the most recognized name in listing management. The Knowledge Graph creates a single source of truth for all business data. Change your hours once and the update pushes to Google, Apple Maps, Bing, Yelp, Facebook, and 200+ other platforms automatically. Holiday hours, seasonal schedules, duplicate suppression, photo distribution — all managed from one dashboard. The analytics show which directories drive actual customer actions: clicks, calls, and direction requests. The downside: cancel Yext and listings revert to pre-Yext data.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Real-time sync to 200+ directories from a single dashboard</h4><p>Change your hours once and it propagates everywhere within hours. No manual logins to 20+ platforms. Holiday hours, seasonal schedules, and multiple service types all managed from one place.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Duplicate listing suppression across partner directories</h4><p>Scans for and removes conflicting listings created by former tenants, automated scrapers, or outdated data. Prevents split review authority across multiple profiles.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Analytics show which directories drive actual customer actions</h4><p>See impressions, clicks, calls, and direction requests per platform. Understand which directories matter — not just which ones have your listing.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: vendor lock-in — cancel and listings revert</h4><p>$499/year minimum with per-location pricing for multi-location businesses. If you cancel, your listings across partner directories revert to their pre-Yext state. Single-location businesses often find Moz Local sufficient at $20/month.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="tool-3" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#3 · $20–$40/MO/LOCATION · ANNUAL</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Moz Local — Best Budget Listing Distribution</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For single-location businesses that need affordable directory sync across the 90+ directories that actually drive traffic.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">Moz Local handles listing distribution at a price that single-location businesses can justify. Enter your business data once and it pushes to 90+ directories. The data aggregator submissions to Factual, Acxiom, Neustar, and Localeze fix errors at the source level — these aggregators feed dozens of downstream directories. Fixing the source fixes the cascade. At $20–$40/month per location, it's roughly half the price of Yext with solid coverage of the directories that account for 90% of local search traffic.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Data aggregator submissions fix errors at the source</h4><p>Fixing Factual, Acxiom, and Localeze cascades corrections to dozens of downstream directories automatically. This is the most efficient listing fix available — most tools skip this entirely.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>$20/month is the most affordable paid listing sync option</h4><p>Half the price of Yext for coverage of the directories that drive 90% of local search traffic. Correct value for single-location businesses.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Duplicate detection and listing health score</h4><p>Flags conflicting listings and gives a single accuracy score for your directory presence. Simple and clean dashboard for business owners without SEO experience.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: 90 directories vs. Yext's 200+, and sync takes 1–4 weeks</h4><p>Listing changes don't propagate instantly. No content creation, GBP posting, or rank tracking included. Purely a listing distribution tool.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="tool-4" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#4 · $39–$59/MO · MONTHLY</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">BrightLocal — Best Listing Audit and Monitoring Platform</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For businesses that want to diagnose listing problems before investing in a distribution tool.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">BrightLocal is not a listing distribution tool — it's a listing audit and monitoring platform. It shows you exactly where your citations are wrong, which directories have outdated data, and how your listing presence compares to competitors. Before you invest in Yext or Moz Local, run a BrightLocal audit. You might find that 90% of your citations are fine and only 5–6 directories need manual fixes — saving months of subscription fees on distribution tools.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Citation audit across 80+ directories with exact inconsistency flagging</h4><p>Every wrong phone number, outdated address, and missing listing flagged with the specific directory name. A precise punch list, not a vague accuracy score.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Geo-grid rank tracking shows Maps position alongside listing health</h4><p>See your Maps ranking position and citation consistency in one dashboard. The combination shows whether listing errors are affecting your local pack positions.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Review monitoring aggregates feedback from Google, Yelp, and Facebook</h4><p>Review velocity and rating are local ranking factors. BrightLocal's monitoring ensures you never miss a review that needs a response.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: audits citations but does not distribute or sync them</h4><p>BrightLocal finds listing problems. It does not fix them automatically. Citation building is a separate paid add-on, and per-location pricing means multi-location costs multiply quickly.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="ba-grid" id="tool-5" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#5 · ~$40/MO ADD-ON · SEMRUSH REQUIRED</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Semrush Listing Management — Best for Teams Already Using Semrush</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For marketing teams that want listing management inside their existing Semrush platform.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">Semrush Listing Management extends the broader Semrush platform with local directory distribution. Distribute your data to 70+ directories, track GBP performance with more depth than Google's native analytics, and monitor local pack appearances for specific keywords at specific zip codes. Makes sense only if your team already pays for Semrush — the listing add-on at ~$40/month on top of a $130+/month Semrush subscription is expensive for listing management alone.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Listing management inside the Semrush platform — eliminates tool sprawl</h4><p>If you're already paying for keyword research, site audits, and rank tracking in Semrush, the listing add-on keeps local SEO in one place.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>GBP insights with more depth than Google's native analytics</h4><p>Impressions, searches, actions, and photo views tracked with trend data and competitor context that Google's dashboard doesn't provide.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Local pack monitoring by keyword and zip code</h4><p>Track whether you appear in the 3-pack for specific queries at specific locations. More precise than standard rank tracking.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: total cost is $170–$230/month when you add the Semrush base</h4><p>That's 4–8x what Moz Local charges for listing distribution alone. Don't pay for Semrush just to get listing management — buy Moz Local at $20/month instead.</p></div></li>
