  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="faq-grid">
      <div class="faq-left">
        <span class="label-pill">FAQ</span>
        <h2 class="h-md">Local listing management, <span class="accent">answered.</span></h2>
        <p>Common questions from local businesses shopping for listing management tools. More? Email <a href="mailto:founder@thestacc.com">founder@thestacc.com</a>.</p>
        <p style="margin-top: 24px;">See more: <a href="/reviews/" class="accent">read tool reviews</a>, <a href="/alternatives/" class="accent">compare alternatives</a>, or <a href="/pricing/" class="accent">view pricing</a>.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is the best local listing management tool in 2026?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">theStacc is our top pick for overall local ranking impact — it creates 30 GBP posts and 30 blog articles per month on autopilot, the content that improves your local pack rankings. For directory sync specifically, Yext ($499/yr) covers 200+ directories and Moz Local ($20/mo) covers 90+ at a budget price.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is local listing management?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Local listing management ensures your business name, address, and phone number is consistent and accurate across all directories, maps, and apps where customers find you. Inconsistent NAP data confuses Google and lowers your local search rankings.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Why does local listing accuracy matter for SEO?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Google cross-references your business data across directories to verify accuracy. Wrong phone numbers, outdated addresses, or duplicate listings with different information all send conflicting signals that lower your local search rankings. Consistent listings strengthen Google's trust in your business data.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is the difference between Yext and Moz Local?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Yext distributes to 200+ directories in real time with duplicate suppression — but reverts listings if you cancel and costs $499/year. Moz Local covers 90+ directories at $20–$40/month with data aggregator submissions. Yext is better for large multi-location businesses; Moz Local is better for single-location businesses on a budget.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Do I need a listing management tool if I have Google Business Profile?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Yes. GBP is one listing. Google cross-references 50–200+ other directories. Apple Maps, Bing, Yelp, Facebook, Healthgrades, and data aggregators all need accurate NAP data. Without a listing tool, you're managing each directory manually — typically dozens of logins across multiple platforms.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What are data aggregators and why do they matter?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Data aggregators (Factual, Acxiom, Neustar, Localeze) collect business data and distribute it to hundreds of downstream directories. If your data is wrong at the aggregator level, errors spread automatically. Moz Local and some Yext plans submit corrections to aggregators directly, fixing the source and cascading corrections downstream.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Can I manage local listings manually?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Yes, but it's time-consuming. The 6 directories that drive most local traffic can be updated manually. For 50–200+ directories, manual management requires hours per update cycle. Moz Local at $20/month makes the math simple: one hour of your time is worth more than the monthly subscription.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
